I have the same happening in Linux and according to a wireshark dump compose uploads the secret from the environment variable via this api endpoint: https://docs.docker.com/reference/api/engine/version/v1.41/#tag/Container/operation/PutContainerArchive

Now when the container starts `/run/secrets` gets created as tmpfs mount hiding the underlying secret. I wonder if it would make sense for podman to not mount `/run/secrets` at all if there is no subscription file or other secret to mount into it. I tried to find the location where `/run/secrets` gets mounted unconditionally but couldn't find it yet.

@baude Do you mind updating the labels to be not windows only? This affects everything not just windows.
